<TITLE> Banani accident victim was a naval officer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com)  The man killed in the Banani level- crossing accident Wednesday has been identified as a naval officer, a railway police officer said Thursday. The deceased was lieutenant commander Hafiz Karim Khan. He was on leave preparatory to retirement. Sub-inspector Zakir Hossain, who prepared a primary investigation report, said another naval officer had identified him. A train rammed into his vehicle, stuck on the rail line, Wednesday. Sub inspector Abdur Rahman of the Railway Police, the investigation officer of the case, said an unnatural death case had been filed first as the deceased could not be identified immediately. Another case was filed against Hafiz Karim Khan, a resident of Khilgaon, with Kamalapur Railway Police Station on charges of reckless driving. Railway police Wednesday said the accident had occurred as Khan was driving on the wrong side to cross the level-crossing resulting in his getting trapped in the tracks. bdnews24.
